  "prompt": "What is an example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users?",
  "response": "A classic example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users is Instagram. When Instagram first launched in 2010, it was specifically designed to be compatible with and optimized for Apple's iOS, particularly the iPhone's camera features. However, Instagram significantly amplified its user base by tapping into Facebook\u2019s massive network.\n\nIn 2012, Facebook acquired Instagram for about $1 billion. This acquisition allowed Instagram to fully leverage Facebook\u2019s extensive user base and integration features. Instagram encouraged users to sign up using their Facebook accounts, which not only made the signup process easier but also permitted users to share their Instagram photos on Facebook. This cross-platform sharing helped Instagram rapidly reach a broader audience by riding on Facebook's then already enormous and still-growing user base, significantly accelerating Instagram's own growth trajectory.\n\nLater, Instagram continued to expand by developing Android and web versions and by further integrating with Facebook\u2019s ad systems, thus maintaining a symbiotic relationship between the two platforms.",
